But you still get to do real journalism.

900
00:43:25.040 --> 00:43:26.160
Please. tell me that you do.

901
00:43:26.200 --> 00:43:28.260
You know what was amazing?

902
00:43:28.680 --> 00:43:32.800
The series you did on the Federal
Reserve when you were the Vanguard.

903
00:43:34.360 --> 00:43:37.900
You read a four-piece series about the
inner workings of the Federal Reserve.

904
00:43:37.901 --> 00:43:39.799
without knowing if you were
ever going to see me again?

905
00:43:39.800 --> 00:43:40.260
I did.

906
00:43:40.540 --> 00:43:41.940
And that's weird that I did that.

907
00:43:42.040 --> 00:43:43.679
Now. hearing you say it. that is weird.

908
00:43:43.680 --> 00:43:45.520
I shouldn't have told you that.

909
00:43:45.620 --> 00:43:46.620
It's nice.

910
00:43:47.080 --> 00:43:48.080
It's really nice.

911
00:43:48.300 --> 00:43:53.260
I've been in long-term relationships with guys who
have never read anything of mine. so it's very nice.

912
00:43:53.620 --> 00:43:54.620
That's appalling.

913
00:43:54.720 --> 00:43:55.080
I know.

914
00:43:55.140 --> 00:43:55.580
It's crazy.

915
00:43:55.880 --> 00:43:59.900
But I can't help it.

916
